Now that the keyframes are converted to grayscale, let's proceed with counting objects in each frame using the object_counter skill.

```json
{
  "analysis": "All 8 keyframes have been converted to grayscale. Now I need to count the objects (coins, enemies, turtles) in each grayscale frame using the object_counter skill. I'll use the command pattern provided in the object_counter skill documentation.",
  "plan": "For each of the 8 keyframes, I'll count coins, enemies, and turtles using the object_counter command. I'll store the results in variables or temporary files to later compile into a CSV.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "for i in {1..8}; do frame=/root/keyframes_$(printf '%03d' $i).png; echo $frame; python3 /root/.claude/skills/object_counter/scripts/count_objects.py --tool count --input_image $frame --object_image /root/coin.png --threshold 0.9 --dedup_min_dist 3; done\n",
      "duration": 10.0
    }
  ]
}
```
